Ask HN: Subtitles with Accumulated Time Error
text: I wanted to add subtitles to an old movie that I have but I only found the Blu-ray version of the subtitles. I thought it would be okay, I would only need to shift all the subtitles a specific amount of time to resync them. But to my surprise, as long as the video progressed, the subtitles were more and more delayed. I can't grasp why this is happening because to my understanding, the time between phrases should be the same, no matter the format of the video. If more frames are added, making the scene longer, the audio would be desynchronized so I don't understand this behaviour. Can anyone enlighten me about what's happening here?

Tell HN: I started using Proton Mail again, I find it much improved
text:
I was a paid subscriber for years, then got tired of it and went back to alternating between Apple Mail and Gmail.

I recently bought a 1 year subscription again and there are several things I now like better:

Most images in emails are 'safe loaded' automatically. There is now a Proton Calendar app for iOS. It seemed like attaching my personal domain was easier than before. The web app seems more responsive.

Show HN: Font Awesome Icon Picker Using AI
text:
I am a big fan and user of Font Awesome icons. Although their search function is pretty neat, sometimes I find it difficult to search for icons related to a particular concept or topic.

As a solution, I have created an app where you can enter any concept or topic and receive the corresponding Font Awesome icon code. Here is an example for the word "prediction":

When I searched for "prediction" using Font Awesome's search, no icons were returned: https://fontawesome.com/search?q=prediction&o=r

However, the app suggested that I should use the "chart-line" icon, which was accurate: https://cookup.ai/o/prediction-font-awesome-icon-picker-usin...

Please try it out and let me know your feedback.
